<h1>Help</h1>

<h2>Key Concepts</h2>
<p><strong>Objectives</strong> are the broad functional areas where the prioritisation team (the UK prioritisation group, aided by the trio) have decided that they want to focus effort in this <strong>Quarter</strong>.</p>
<p>Each objective can have multiple <strong>Key Results</strong>. Key results should be concrete i.e. either a measurable impact on a metric (e.g. reduce bad order rate to 1%) or a deliverable (e.g. deliver first version of restaurant management tool).  It's expected that objectives may span quarters but key results should deliver within a quarter. Each key result will be aligned with a <strong>Company Goal</strong>.</p>
<p>Each key result may have one or more <strong>Deliverable</strong>. These will be a mix of product discovery items (which test a hypothesis) and delivery items (which build functionality).</p>
<p>Each deliverable will have a <strong> Team</strong> assigned to it and will be prioritised against other work for the team.</p>
<p>As the quarter progresses the teams will provide regular <strong>Updates</strong> on progress of each of their deliverables. Programme management will collate this feedback and provide a weekly summary report to the exec and UK management team on progress of the key results for each objective.</p>
